  "created_at": "2026-03-03T13:10:00Z",
  "source": "claude-advisor",
  "edge_hypothesis": "ALMA (Arnaud Legoux Moving Average) uses a Gaussian-weighted calculation that minimizes lag while maintaining smoothness — mathematically distinct from EMA. In ranging markets (CHOP > 50), when CCI reaches extreme values (<-100 or >100) and price reverts toward ALMA, this captures overextension-to-mean-reversion. ALMA's smoother curve should produce cleaner reversion targets than EMA, reducing whipsaw entries. CCI extremes have proven profitable in CCI Chop Fade v2 (PF=1.255, ALL regimes) — this tests whether ALMA as the reversion anchor improves on EMA-based approaches.",
  "regime_assumption": "ranging",
  "target_assets": ["ETH", "BTC"],
  "target_timeframes": ["4h"],
